org.hibernate.ogm.type.descriptor.impl

Class Iso8601DateTypeDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.type.descriptor.java.AbstractTypeDescriptor<Date>
      • org.hibernate.type.descriptor.java.DateTypeDescriptor
        • org.hibernate.ogm.type.descriptor.impl.Iso8601DateTypeDescriptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, JavaTypeDescriptor<Date>

    public class Iso8601DateTypeDescriptor
extends DateTypeDescriptor
    Converts Dates into ISO8601-compliant strings and vice versa. The strings either contain date or time information or both. The serialized strings contain no time zone information and represent the given dates in UTC.

    Implementation note: The actual work is delegated to JAXB's DatatypeConverter which creates ISO8601-compliant strings. This is ok since JAXB is part of the JDK.

    Author:
    Gunnar Morling
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
